Here’s a set of **standard Word formatting guidelines** you can apply to your `prd.docx` (PSD) to ensure consistency and readability:

---

## 1. Document-Wide Settings

* **Page Size & Margins**

  * A4 (210 × 297 mm)
  * Margins: 1″ (2.54 cm) on all sides
* **Line Spacing**

  * Body text: 1.15
  * Before/After paragraph spacing: 6 pt before, 6 pt after
* **Alignment**

  * Body text: Justified
  * Headings: Left‑aligned

---

## 2. Font Family & Sizes

| Element             | Font Family      | Font Size | Style       |
| ------------------- | ---------------- | --------- | ----------- |
| Body Text           | Calibri or Arial | 11 pt     | Regular     |
| Section Headings H1 | Calibri or Arial | 18 pt     | Bold        |
| Sub‑Headings H2     | Calibri or Arial | 14 pt     | Bold        |
| Sub‑Sub H3          | Calibri or Arial | 12 pt     | Bold Italic |
| Captions & Notes    | Calibri or Arial | 10 pt     | Italic      |
| Table Text          | Calibri or Arial | 10 pt     | Regular     |

---

## 3. Heading Styles

* **H1 (e.g., “1. Introduction”)**

  * 18 pt, Bold, All Caps or Title Case
  * 24 pt spacing after
* **H2 (e.g., “2. Product Overview”)**

  * 14 pt, Bold, Title Case
  * 18 pt spacing after
* **H3 (e.g., “2.1 In‑Scope”)**

  * 12 pt, Bold Italic, Sentence case
  * 12 pt spacing after

> ⚙️ *Use Word’s built‑in Heading 1/2/3 styles so you can auto‑generate the Table of Contents.*

---

## 4. Text Emphasis

* **Bold** for key terms, requirement IDs (e.g., **FR‑1**), section titles
* *Italic* for examples, notes, captions
* `Monospaced` (Courier New or Consolas, 10 pt) for code snippets or inline file references

---

## 5. Lists & Numbering

* **Bullet lists:** round bullets, 0.25″ indent
* **Numbered lists:** Arabic numerals (1., 1.1, 1.1.1), 0.25″ indent per level
* **Requirement tables:** use a simple 1 pt grid, banded rows (light gray on alternate rows)

---

## 6. Tables & Figures

* **Table captions:** 10 pt Italic, above table
* **Figure captions:** 10 pt Italic, below figure
* **Table header row:** Bold, center‑aligned, 11 pt, light shading (15% gray)

---

## 7. Footer & Header

* **Header:** Document title (left) + version/date (right), 10 pt
* **Footer:** Page number centered, 10 pt

---

## 8. Colors & Highlights

* Keep body text in black.
* Use one accent color (e.g., dark blue) sparingly for call‑outs or status indicators.
* Avoid excessive highlighting—reserve for very important notes only.

---

Applying these specs will give your PSD a clean, professional look and make it easy to navigate and review.
